author: thrantal
msg: WICKET-1745: Slowly getting rid of raw Model usage.
I'm not too happy with this solution, but am shipping it in anyway after tossing it around for several hours. Feedbacks and fixes are most welcome!

(One) problem is that Model.of() is traditionally used both for Model.of(List<T>) and Model.of(List<? extends T>) and you cannot just use a wildcarded version in place of T. Overloading of() doesn't solve this either, because the methods would have the same erasure.
